# Code ownership and review responsibility for Nojoin (GOV-001).
#
# GitHub auto-requests a review from the owner of every changed path when a
# pull request is opened. Matching is last-match-wins: the catch-all is first
# and the most specific subsystem rules are last.
#
# Nojoin is currently maintained by a single person, so every subsystem maps to
# the sole maintainer. The map still documents the responsibility boundaries and
# is forward-compatible: when a co-maintainer joins, add their handle to the
# relevant lines without restructuring the file.

# --- Default owner for everything not matched more specifically ---
*                                   @Valtora

# --- Backend / API ---
/backend/api/**                     @Valtora

# --- Worker / ML and the processing pipeline ---
/backend/worker/**                  @Valtora
/backend/processing/**              @Valtora

# --- Database migrations (sensitive: one checked-in head, no rename/delete) ---
/backend/alembic/**                 @Valtora

# --- Frontend and browser capture ---
/frontend/src/**                    @Valtora
/frontend/src/lib/capture/**        @Valtora

# --- Security-sensitive code and policy ---
/docs/SECURITY.md                   @Valtora
/backend/core/security.py           @Valtora
/backend/core/encryption.py         @Valtora
/backend/api/deps.py                @Valtora
/backend/api/v1/endpoints/login.py  @Valtora

# --- Deployment, containers, and CI/release pipelines ---
/docker/**                          @Valtora
/docker-compose*.yml                @Valtora
/.github/workflows/**               @Valtora

# --- Documentation ---
/docs/**                            @Valtora
*.md                                @Valtora
